01:01:28.480 --> 01:01:30.430
had them keep a journal.

01:01:30.430 --> 01:01:32.990
And then I told them I wanted
them to explain--

01:01:32.990 --> 01:01:33.850
the journal they liked.

01:01:33.850 --> 01:01:35.150
But then I said, on the
homeworks, I want you to

01:01:35.150 --> 01:01:37.590
explain your reasoning
so that it reads.

01:01:37.590 --> 01:01:40.460
It's not just hence and
thus and therefore.

01:01:40.460 --> 01:01:42.250
And they said, well, why
we have to do that?

01:01:42.250 --> 01:01:43.080
We're physics students.

01:01:43.080 --> 01:01:45.280
I said, well, later on, you're
going to have to communicate

01:01:45.280 --> 01:01:46.640
your answers to someone.

01:01:46.640 --> 01:01:49.810
They said, oh, we'll just hire
someone who does that.

01:01:49.810 --> 01:01:52.550
So then I said to them, "well,
how are you going to explain

01:01:52.550 --> 01:01:54.470
it to that person?

01:01:54.470 --> 01:01:59.487
How will they know?" I said, "oh
you're going--" "oh, I'll

01:01:59.487 --> 01:02:01.470
explain it to them." I said,
"oh, so you are explaining

01:02:01.470 --> 01:02:01.740
something?"

01:02:01.740 --> 01:02:04.050
They said "oh, no." Somebody
said, "oh, well, actually that

01:02:04.050 --> 01:02:06.510
person will understand it
already." So then I said to

01:02:06.510 --> 01:02:10.550
them, "well, so that person
understands it already and can

01:02:10.550 --> 01:02:11.480
communicate it.

01:02:11.480 --> 01:02:13.135
And you just understand it.

01:02:13.135 --> 01:02:15.740
Who are people going
to turn? "

01:02:15.740 --> 01:02:17.840
So only then did they agree that
it was a good thing to

01:02:17.840 --> 01:02:20.480
actually write problem sets
so they could communicate.

01:02:20.480 --> 01:02:22.360
So that's something you
can teach in any

01:02:22.360 --> 01:02:23.780
